  "text": "In addition, in the first incubation, the effect of salinity on ammonium nitrogen was more obvious than nitrate nitrogen. This was because urea was not transformed into nitrate nitrogen fully. Studies indicated that the proportion of urea transforming into ammonium is 28.9% in 3-7 h after urea applied to soil and 63.85-76.50% in 24 h while the significant accumulation of nitrate nitrogen occurred about 96h after urea was applied [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
